<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA (Desoxyribonucleic Acid)</a> - A <a href="#molecule">molecule</a> (<a href="#nucleic_acid">nucleic acid</a>) which carries most of the genetic instructions used in the development, function and reproduction of all known living organisms and many <a href="#virus">viruses</a>. DNA is the primary compenent of <a href="#chromosome">chromosomes</a>.
